Procedure.description:
PROCEDURE PURPOSE: to perform a MTG-I Station Keeing Manoeuvre
PROCEDURE VERSION: 34 RESPONSIBILITY: Christian Bihr LAST MODIFIED DATE: 09.11.2022
CHANGE HISTORY: [CBi 2022/11/09 EUM v. 33.0]
Implementation of SATMAN Version 4 - 31/08/2022 - FOM06 Changes: @All / AIM#214530: import EUM Procedure attached from AIM (which is EUM v.29) @P.6.A3+A4/AIM#223175: added RW drift setting
EUM edits: Removals of following steps as per EUM/OPS-MTG/VWG/22/1329528 -P.5.A1 FCI Work Plan stop (including wheels APC) -P.5.A2 LI to WAIT -P.5.A3 Set Attenuation MAX on GeoSAR (via N_GSR_I011, PAF) -P.7.A4 Restore GeoSAR -P.7.A5 Switch LI from WAIT to OPERATIONAL mode -P.7.A6 Start FCI -removed variable for attenuation -deleted step P.7.A3 (GOTO END) which was implemented for SVT-i1-v3 only and Label in step P.9 -added varaible for RW_drift_setting as per SATMAN change -added variable Upload_torque to specify solstice or equinox case (missing in SATMAN procedure) - AR6144 , -step P.7.A1.A2.A1 'set variable step' created for the operator to set it to either equinox or solstice -step P.7.A1.A2.A2 to call N_AOC_i500 and set the argument 'case' to "#PR!!Upload_torque" added -new step P.7 is now handling the option for RW drift setting if SKM-NS or WO (AIM 223175) -option added in step P.2.A2 via new variable OOP_Update to skip OOP upload for special cases (AR6054 and EUM/MTG/VWG/22/1305658 p.14)
PROCEDURE OBJECTIVES: This procedure is a satellite level procedure putting the Satellite in configuration for SKM. When ready, it calls the PF level procedures executing the NS, EW or Wheel-Offloading manoeuvre.
PROCEDURE OVERVIEW: It consists of 3 branches selectable by arguments "Manouver".
PROCEDURE PRE-CONDITIONS: the FDS product to complete a manoeuver shall be ready and Available in MCS (PAF_MAN, PAF_SKM, PAF_OOP )
PROCEDURE CONSTRAINTS: None
SPACECRAFT CONFIGURATION: Sat is in NOM/SBM AOCS is FPM PL ON and OPERATIONAL
GROUND SEGMENT CONFIGURATION: None
Procedure.title: Perform SKM manoeuvre
Procedure.author: nevado_OPRE
Procedure.hierarchy: Child Procedures: MTI1::N_AOC_0751 called by steps: P.4.A3 MTI1::N_SYS_I110 called by steps: P.6.A1 Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_0110 called by steps: P.6.A2 MTI1::N_SYS_I111 called by steps: P.6.B1 Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_0111 called by steps: P.6.B2 Default::N_SYS_I112 called by steps: P.6.C2 Default:NomSysPF::N_SYS_0112 called by steps: P.6.C3 MTI1::N_AOC_I500 called by steps: P.7.A1.A2.A2, P.7.A1.A2.A3
Procedure.history:
[DNe 07.03.2023] Re-verified
[DNe 2023/02/27 EUM v. 34.0] Re-verified to call N_SYS_0111 with its updated argument list with the goal of updating RW speed targets dynamically from FDS PAFs
[CBi 2022/11/09 EUM v. 33.0] Implementation of SATMAN Version 4 - 31/08/2022 - FOM06 Changes: @All / AIM#214530: import EUM Procedure attached from AIM (which is EUM v.29) @P.6.A3+A4/AIM#223175: added RW drift setting
EUM edits: Removals of following steps as per EUM/OPS-MTG/VWG/22/1329528 -P.5.A1 FCI Work Plan stop (including wheels APC) -P.5.A2 LI to WAIT -P.5.A3 Set Attenuation MAX on GeoSAR (via N_GSR_I011, PAF) -P.7.A4 Restore GeoSAR -P.7.A5 Switch LI from WAIT to OPERATIONAL mode -P.7.A6 Start FCI
-removed variable for attenuation -deleted step P.7.A3 (GOTO END) which was implemented for SVT-i1-v3 only and Label in step P.9 -added varaible for RW_drift_setting as per SATMAN change -added variable Upload_torque to specify solstice or equinox case (missing in SATMAN procedure) - AR6144 , -step P.7.A1.A2.A1 'set variable step' created for the operator to set it to either equinox or solstice -step P.7.A1.A2.A2 to call N_AOC_i500 and set the argument 'case' to "#PR!!Upload_torque" added -new step P.7 is now handling the option for RW drift setting if SKM-NS or WO (AIM 223175) -option added in step P.2.A2 via new variable OOP_Update to skip OOP upload for special cases (AR6054 and EUM/MTG/VWG/22/1305658 p.14)
[CBi 2022/09/07 EUM v. 32.0] -Added sanity check P.4.A1 for SimOffset = 0 for manoeuvres. -removed step previously added (C_SYS_0200) and removed PL_ON procedure variable -added GOTO End of Procedure step P.7.A3 to skip PL activation as this will be dealt with at a later stage, to decide, which parent procedure to be used to activate PL after manoeuvre. -missing values and default values in call to procedure FCI in step P.7.A6: to get the procedure verified and saved w/o errors, needed to assert safety values, when possible, for arguments (e.g. set date in the past, start time to 0 etc.)
[RTi 2022/08/02 EUM v. 31.0] - assigned Default value to argument Manoeuvre to let this procedure called by C_SYS_0200. - added in step P.7 the option to skip the FCI and LI restart if coming form the C_SYS_0200 due to the APC managment. also added a new PL_ON procedure variable.
[CBi 2022/06/10 EUM v. 30.0] Re-verified to account for changes in N_AOC_0751
DNe 12.04.2022 v.29 Corrected P.3.A6 Closing also LV_A1
RTi 2022/03/21 v.27 changes: added step P.4.A1 to apply an Offset to the input Time parameter generated by FDS, to be used only in Simulation.
CBi 2022/02/16 v.24 Changes: For RID1218, case step P.3.A6.A2.A5 added for 5th RCT selection only applicable in EW case
RTi 2022/02/02 v.23 changes: step P.6.C2 corrected call to N_SYS_0112 in proceudre arguments with EPHM_SIN_HALF_L=#PR!!EPHM_SIN_HALF_L
------- CBi 2022/01/13 v.22 Changes: -deleted variables and steps P.4.A2/A3 UNIX_START_TREF, OBT_START_TREF -Step P.4.A1 changed from calling N_AOC_0750 to N_AOC_0751 -assigned values to START_TREF and T_OFFSET from PAF - #DVAR!MTI1:D_OBT_S_TREF assigned in P.6.A2/B2/C2 for START_TREF - #DVAR!MTI1:D_OBT_T_OFFSET_INT_SKM in P.6.A2/B2/C2 for T_OFFSET

DNe 21/10/2021 - Creation of Time Format Management section (P.4) - Variable OBT_START_TREF created - Variable UNIX_START_TREF created - Population of arguments in call to N_SYS_0110 - Population of arguments in call to N_SYS_0111 - Creation of Section Conversion of FDS to enumeration values (P.3)

DNe 29/10/2021 Argument TC4delay set to 60 instead of 30
